name: Rumah Gadang, Minangkabau.
description:
Rumah Gadang is derrivatively translated into Big House in Minangkabau, Rumah Gadang are the traditional homes of the Minangkabau in West Sumatra, Indonesia. 
The architecture, construction, internal and external decoration, and the functions of the house reflect the culture and values of the Minangkabau. A Rumah Gadang serves as a residence, a hall for family meetings, and for ceremonial activities.
